OL,3,GStrathclyde
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FCloudy and patchy rain soon
OL,6,Fclearing away eastwards this morning.
OL,7,FThen mainly dry with bright spells
OL,8,Falthough a few showers developing this
OL,9,Fafternoon, mainly Argyll. Freshening
OL,10,Fsouthwesterly winds across Mull.
OL,11,
OL,12,CTonight:FCentral Belt and the south
OL,13,Fhaving a mainly dry evening and night.
OL,14,FArgyll will be cloudier with a few
OL,15,Fshowers. Fresh southwesterly winds
OL,16,Falong coastal Argyll.
OL,17,
OL,18,CMonday:FDry in the south but a showers
OL,19,Facross Argyll, and the Central Belt at
OL,20,Ffirst. Some bright spells but rather
OL,21,Fcloudy.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
